\b swiss ebook design stands as a methodology for reflowable text layouts
\b0 . It uses principles of swiss graphic design, which have been adapted to ebooks, and 
\b aims at clarity, hierarchy, rhythm and readability
\b0 . \
It can be used for both non-fiction and fiction (it is beneficial to fiction too since small details make a big difference), and is quite simple to understand. Once you get it, creating (quite complex) reflowable ebook layouts is super-easy. \
It is not suited to heavily designed ebooks (fixed-layout was made for this) but it allows designers to create good-looking text-heavy books. It also fixes a lot of problems/limitations and helps build hierarchy.\
Last but not least, it works in EPUB and Amazon KF8.\
\
