\b\fs36 \cf2 \
Block Management
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \
In swiss ebook design, 
\b content is managed as blocks piling up
\b0 ; there is no idea of floating blocks (
\i\b float:left
\b0 \cf2 ;
\i0 \cf2 ) except drop caps. \
It doesn't matter you use text-indent method or block method (line-break), this methodology works with both. \
Basically, you are trying to 
\b manage flowing blocks in a pseudo grid system
\b0 . \
In swiss ebook design, \
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\ri-2860\qj
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}pure layout is coded using div tag. Div tag is neutral, its values are the same as body's (it works like a reboot). For specific divs, subclasses are created.\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}pure semantic is coded using HTML semantic tags (h, p, ul/ol + li, etc.)\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}img and blockquote tags are considered hybrid, they are used for layout 
\i and
\i0  semantic. \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\ri-2860\qj
\cf2 \
Besides, 
\b designers can change scale
\b0 :\
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\ri-2860\qj
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}
\b superblocks
\b0 , which help regroup semantic tags in order to achieve rhythm and hierarchy.\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}
\b blocks
\b0  (HTML semantic tags)\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}
\b subblocks
\b0 , which are spans actually (highlights or drop caps for example, but links may be managed as subblocks too (CSS border or background)).\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
