\b Blocks can be differentiated in order to achieve hierarchy
\b0 . In other words, they get their own CSS properties like background-color, margin or padding, font-size, width, text color (in shades of gray since we must take e-ink readers into account), etc. \
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\qj

\b\fs36 \cf2 \
Whitespace
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \

\b Whitespace is used for hierarchy, readability and rhythm
\b0 . It is expressed using 
\b proportions
\b0 /ratios. Hence, anything CSS related to font and margin/padding is finely tuned. We will discuss that point later.\
It is working with block management and pseudo grid system. As a result, whitespace includes 
\i\b page-breaks
\i0\b0  (before, after, inside) so that you can take care of rhythm and blocks of content (example for short blockquotes: \{page-break-inside: avoid; page-break-before: auto; page-break-after: auto\} so that blockquotes shall be rendered as real blocks + it forces a pause before the block, a pause which won't happen inside the block and break the flow).\
Finally, 
\b shades of gray
\b0  are part of whitespace because they can be used to build visual hints. For example, if you are designing a layout for non-fiction, you can add numbers (part + subparts) in a specific block (using div) where text is colored a light shade of gray, to make it a subtle visual hint expressing hierarchy. \

\b Whitespace can be considered an invisible block
\b0 .\
\
\pard\tx0\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\qj

\b\fs36 \cf2 Pseudo Grid System
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \
PGS is a 
\b subtle layer of hierarchy, some kind of interface to the content
\b0 . It works like a playground in which you pile blocks and whitespace (invisible blocks). There is no notion of vertically-fixed (y index) guides, it all depends on blocks of content. But that doesn't mean horizontal guides are fixed (x index). \
In fact, 
\b guides
\b0  on x-index 
\b can be set as you wish
\b0 . Again, it is all about visual hints: it 
\b must help readers understand hierarchy, it mustn't show
\b0 . \
PGS is very 
\b architectural
\b0  in some ways. Think of it as a canvas in which you are creating a building (upside down since it is reflowable text). It must remain stable, hence your central column (it doesn't have to be HTML tag p, it can be a long blockquote or image) has to be at least 80 or 86% of the grid's width (because of smartphone screens). You can add columns to the right and/or the left but you must take balance into account so that it doesn't collapse. 
\b You don't even have to consider it something symmetric, it is all about balance
\b0 . If your grid layout looks and feels safe, it is alright.  \
That is how it simply works, your grid is some kind of ruled paper that helps build hierarchy. Idea implied is: "
\b from chaos to order
\b0 ".\
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\qj

\b\fs36 \cf2 Minimalism, elementarism, constructivism
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \
To sum things up, you are trying to 
\b remove the unnecessary and emphasize the necessary
\b0 . In other words, you are 
\b managing fundamental elements of style in a functional and simple way
\b0 .\
This is why you must pay attention to type; typeface is one of the most fundamental elements of visual communication. Don't waste anything,
\b  find harmony
\b0 . \
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\qj

\b\fs36 \cf2 Typefaces/fonts
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \
Your goal is clarity, simplicity and universality \'97though you are allowed to break this "rule" if you are creating a layout for fiction and/or wish to add some personality to your book\'97. \
Typeface mustn't be expressive in itself, it must be an 
\b unobtrusive instrument of expression
\b0 . \
More importantly, 
\b font-size is used as a tool for readability, impact and rhythm
\b0 . It is all about contrast, impact and hints about the hierarchy of the presented data. Think huge for entry points, introductory paragraphs, conclusions or pillars of reflection. You are trying to 
\b guide the reader's eyes through the page
\b0 , to create an interface to the content. \
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\qj

\b\fs36 \cf2 Photography
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \
Photography portrays reality, but it can also be used as a pillar for your layout. Typically, a photograph is massive, it is a huge block being very stable. So you can pile quite a lot of other blocks on it. As a result, it
\b  can serve balance in the pseudo grid system
\b0 . That is the reason why we are using HTML img tag in a hybrid manner, because we can make smart use of pictures (the same goes for blockquote for different reasons). \
\
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\qj

