\b\fs36 \cf2 Additional notes
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\qj
\cf2 \
\pard\tx200\tx280\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\fi280\ri-2860\qj
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}use relative values (i.e. em or % in the CSS)\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}forget float: left; (except drop caps). It is all about blocks piling up, only whitespace can be added sideways. \
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}since variation in font-sizes may not help readers enough sometimes, you must find other ways to differentiate types of content (background colors, text-align, etc.)\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}hyphens happen. Don't dare imagine fighting them, you are already losing. Use HTML tag shy if you want to manage them more cleverly. \
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}If there is no reason not to align left (except huge blocks such as paragraphs which must absolutely be justified in order to build the grid, or style effects, etc.), align left. That will fix 90% of hyphenation problems. \
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}Rendering engines will always manage blocks of content differently from you. Page-break-inside seems to be the most efficient tool to achieve rhythm and readability. \
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}Standard font-size for on-screen reading is 1em (16px or 12pt). \
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}Max font-size variation/delta that can be used efficiently is 0.8 to 2.5 (for default font-size = 1em).\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}avoid using more than 8 columns in the pseudo grid system since more will make it useless (too many guides for the reader to take into account).\
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}though you may think you must respect strict rules, feeling is one important part of swiss ebook design. If it looks good, it is alright. \
{\listtext	
\f2 \uc0\u9642 
\f0 	}once this methodology mastered, it is possible to design a fully working advanced layout for complex content in less than 30 minutes.\
{\listtext	
